  "texts": [
    "IntroductionChatGPT, the OpenAI chatbot released in November 2022, has ignited significant academic and media interest.",
    "While chatbot technology existed before, recent advances in AI, driven by substantial resource investment, have ushered in a paradigm shift.",
    "ChatGPT leverages advanced deep learning techniques and extensive data training to generate humanlike responses to user inputs [1].",
    "The OpenAI website describes it as capable of engaging in dialogue, answering follow-up questions, recognizing errors, and rejecting inappropriate requests [2].With over 100 million users in its first two months, excitement is brewing around ChatGPT's potential across diverse societal domains, encompassing academia, commerce, professional settings, and personal life [4].",
    "A multitude of applications are being explored, spanning marketing, advertising, consulting, customer service, and finance [10]."
  ],
